articles.author: Reuters
articles.title: 'Rudely trampling on international trade rules': Chinese media beat drum against US
articles.description: China's state media continued a barrage of criticism of the United States on Saturday as their tit-for-tat trade war escalated, while seeking to reassure readers the Chinese economy remains in strong shape.

articles.author: Reuters
articles.title: Lawsuits accuse Tesla's Musk of fraud over tweets, going-private proposal
articles.description: Tesla and Chief Executive Elon Musk were sued twice on Friday by investors who said they fraudulently engineered a scheme to squeeze short-sellers.

articles.author: Kelly Olsen
articles.title: The US-China trade war is worrying some Hong Kong-owned manufacturers, CEO says
articles.description: Hong Kong-owned factories in China are growing concerned about the escalating U.S.-China trade war. Some are even thinking about shifting operations elsewhere, one CEO said.

articles.author: Reuters
articles.title: Trump says progress made toward trade deal with Mexico, but 'Canada must wait'
articles.description: "Canada must wait. Their Tariffs and Trade Barriers are far too high. Will tax cars if we can't make a deal!" U.S. President Donald Trump said.

articles.author: Lauren Hirsch
articles.title: President of major Papa John's franchise organization: 'We believe it is time for the founder to move on'
articles.description: A major Papa Johns franchisee group that represents roughly half the North American system is urging  the chain's founder, John Schnatter, to move on from the company.

articles.author: Patti Domm
articles.title: Turkey fallout could continue to hit global markets, as Erdogan 'hangs tough'
articles.description: Turkey's collapsing currency and reeling economy have fallout for other emerging markets and expose vulnerabilities at some European banks, but strategists do not now see it as a trigger for a broader banking or financial crisis.

articles.author: Jeff Cox
articles.title: Workers see their paychecks get smaller as inflation continues to rise
articles.description: While the rest of the economy pointed higher in July, American workers took a step backwards.  Hourly and weekly earnings actually declined on the month when factoring in the rise in cost of living, according to figures the Labor Department released Friday.

articles.author: Jacob Pramuk
articles.title: Why Trump is attacking Turkey with sanctions and tariffs
articles.description: Trump's moves against Turkey come at least in part in response to simmering conflicts between the two countries over military cooperation and the U.S. push for pastor Andrew Brunson's release.

articles.author: Alexandra Gibbs
articles.title: US futures slide as political concerns keep investors on edge
articles.description: U.S. stock index futures fell deep into the red ahead of Fridayâ€™s open, following negative sentiment in markets overseas.

articles.author: Karen Gilchrist
articles.title: Ask yourself this question every six months to make sure your career's on track
articles.description: If the answer's yes, it could be time to make a change.
